I love the cuisine in the original George & Son restaurant in Scottsdale, so I decided to check this newly-opened branch in north Phoenix.
It is conveniently located in the Deer Valley Towne Square shopping complex along the 101, flanked by 27th Avenue and 31st Avenue; the restaurant is closer to the 31st Avenue end.
The interior of the restaurant is spacious, with modern decor, and has a full bar.
And you'll be hard-pressed to find friendlier staff anywhere!
The menu offers familiar Chinese restaurant items and the food is prepared in the same delicious flavoring style and with similar friendly prices as the original restaurant along Via Linda in Scottsdale.
I'm glad they opened this branch since I often come to this area for movies at the AMC in the complex and for shopping in the nearby Costco, and now have a really decent place to eat and relax during such trips.

